  "id": "019cf625-7dd3-7a72-90bd-3b3cc32b50b7",
  "content": "(edge.relation.clone(), \"incoming\".into()));\n        }\n    }\n\n    let mut neighbors = Vec::new();\n    for entry in &traversed {\n        if entry.id == uuid { continue; } // skip self\n        let (relation, direction) = edge_info\n            .get(&entry.id)\n            .cloned()\n            .unwrap_or((\"transitive\".into(), \"outgoing\".into()));\n        neighbors.push(NeighborDto {\n            id: entry.id.to_string(),\n            content: entry.content.chars().take(200).collect(), // preview\n            relation,\n            direction,\n            score: None,\n            source_file: entry.metadata.source_file.clone(),\n            content_role: entry.metadata.content_role.clone(),\n            source_origin: entry.metadata.source_origin.clone(),\n        });\n    }\n\n    let count = neighbors.len();\n    Ok(Json(json!({ \"neighbors\": neighbors, \"count\": count })))\n}\n```\n\nRegister the route in `dashboard/mod.rs` router alongside existing routes like `entries/{entry_id}/history`: `.route(\"/api/dashboard/entries/{entry_id}/neighbors\", get(entry_neighbors))`\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Update existing handlers to include `content_role`/`source_origin` in JSON responses**\n\nThe `DocumentReader` component reads `entry.metadata.content_role` and the `GraphControls` component reads `node.content_role`/`node.source_origin`. These fields must appear in the server JSON responses.\n\n**Update `entry_detail_handler`** (dashboard/mod.rs ~line 642) — add new fields to the metadata object:\n\n```rust\n\"metadata\": {\n    \"source_file\": entry.metadata.source_file,",
